==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sequela
<hw>Se*que"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Sequelae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a follower, a result,
from <ets>sequit</ets> to follow.]</ety> <def>One who, or that which,
follows.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An adherent, or a band or
sect of adherents.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Coleridge and his
<xex>sequela</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>G. P. Marsh.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>That
which follows as the logical result of reasoning; inference; conclusion;
suggestion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sequelae</qex>, or thoughts suggested by the preceding
aphorisms.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(c)</sd> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A morbid phenomenon left as the
result of a disease; a disease resulting from another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sequence</ent>⟦br⟧
